description:
The Story of Creation in LEGOÂ®.  Made to commemorate Catholic Schools Week 2008.

I'm quite amazed at the response that this video has received.  The video has been shown in schools and churches.  It has been viewed over 18,000 times (as of 7/6/10). I have been contacted by churches and creationist organizations about it.  I'd like to clear up some things.  I am not a believer in intelligent design.  I made this video as a visual representation of a biblical story.  This is not to be taken literally at all.  I have many opinions about the bible and religion in general.  I consider myself an agnostic atheist.  For those who don't know what this means, I am a person who does not believe in a God, but I don't deny that there could be.  I personally think that creationism is a fundamentally flawed belief. 

I have little else to say.  I encourage you to take a class in the history of the bible and the context in which it was written.  Study science, etc, etc... It's fascinating.
